WEBVTT

00:02.211 --> 00:03.884
(BLEATING)

00:06.423 --> 00:07.970
Mabel, do you believe in ghosts?

00:08.175 --> 00:09.597
I believe you're a big dork.

00:09.760 --> 00:10.852
(LAUGHING)

00:11.053 --> 00:12.100
(GRUNTING)

00:12.596 --> 00:13.688
Soos, Wendy!

00:13.889 --> 00:15.015
(PANTING)

00:15.682 --> 00:16.604
What's up, Mr. Pines?

00:16.808 --> 00:19.482
I'm heading out. You two are gonna
wash the bathrooms, right?

00:19.645 --> 00:21.192
- Yes, sir!
- Absolutely not.

00:21.396 --> 00:22.272
(LAUGHING)

00:22.439 --> 00:24.112
You stay out of trouble.

00:25.484 --> 00:27.452
Hey, guys. What's this?

00:28.028 --> 00:29.405
Secret ladder to the roof?

00:29.613 --> 00:31.661
Uh, I don't think Mr. Pines
would like that.

00:31.865 --> 00:32.912
I232:?

00:33.116 --> 00:34.709
- Huh?
- You're freaking me out, dude.

00:34.910 --> 00:36.207
Can we actually go up there?

00:36.411 --> 00:38.960
Sure we can. Roof time! Roof time!

00:39.122 --> 00:40.749
ALL: (CHANTING)
Roof time! Roof time!

00:41.625 --> 00:42.592
(GROANING)

00:45.963 --> 00:46.930
(DIPPER GRUNTING)

00:47.631 --> 00:48.928
All right! Check it out.

00:49.132 --> 00:50.224
- Whoa!
- Whoa! Cool!

00:50.717 --> 00:51.639
(MABEL LAUGHS)

00:51.802 --> 00:53.349
Did you put all this stuff up here?

00:53.554 --> 00:57.400
I may or may not sneak up here
during work, all the time, every day.

00:58.684 --> 00:59.651
(GRUNTING)

01:01.019 --> 01:02.020
Yes!

01:02.229 --> 01:03.606
- All right.
- Me first!

01:06.233 --> 01:07.200
(ALARM BLARING)

01:08.485 --> 01:09.987
Jackpot! High five!

01:11.822 --> 01:13.199
Don't leave me hanging!

01:14.491 --> 01:15.458
BOTH: Ha!

01:16.159 --> 01:17.285
Hey, it's my friends!

01:18.620 --> 01:19.872
THOMPSON: Wendy.

01:20.080 --> 01:22.549
Uh, you guys aren't gonna tell Stan
about this, are you?

01:26.878 --> 01:28.050
Later, dorks.

01:28.255 --> 01:29.177
(GRUNTING)

01:32.134 --> 01:33.135
(HEAVY METAL MUSIC PLAYING)

01:33.343 --> 01:34.310
THOMPSON: Let's get out of here!

01:34.511 --> 01:35.387
- NATE: Whoo!
- Yeah!

01:35.596 --> 01:36.643
Later, Wendy!

01:36.805 --> 01:37.806
(LAUGHING)

01:38.015 --> 01:39.141
Ah, good times.

01:39.349 --> 01:41.317
- Uh-oh!
- What?

01:41.560 --> 01:43.858
Somebody's in love.

01:44.271 --> 01:47.024
Yeah, right,
I just think Wendy's cool, okay?

01:47.232 --> 01:49.951
It's not like I lay awake at night
thinking about her.

01:53.030 --> 01:53.997
Uh-oh!

01:55.324 --> 01:57.292
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

02:35.614 --> 02:38.163
Random dance party for no reason!

02:38.325 --> 02:39.247
(DANCE MUSIC PLAYING)

02:39.451 --> 02:42.830
<i>Go, go, g0, 90, 90, 9019019Â°-</i>

02:46.958 --> 02:47.880
Dipper.

02:48.043 --> 02:49.465
Huh? What? Yes? Yeah?

02:49.836 --> 02:50.837
Aren't you gonna get in on this?

02:51.004 --> 02:52.756
I don't really dance.

02:52.923 --> 02:56.348
Yeah, you do! Mom used to
dress him up in a lamb costume

02:56.551 --> 02:59.646
and make him do the lamby dance.

02:59.805 --> 03:02.058
Now is not the time to talk
about the lamby dance.

03:02.265 --> 03:05.644
Lamb costume? Whoa!
Is there, like, little ears and a tail, or...

03:05.852 --> 03:06.774
Well. Uh...

03:06.978 --> 03:10.278
Dipper would prance around
and sing a song about grazing.

03:10.440 --> 03:11.908
(CUCKOO CLOCK CHIMES)

03:12.859 --> 03:13.826
Hey, look at that!

03:14.027 --> 03:15.825
Quitting time!
The gang's waiting for me.

03:16.029 --> 03:19.750
Hey, wait! Maybe I could,
or we could, come with you?

03:19.950 --> 03:23.375
Ooh! I don't know.
My friends are pretty intense.

03:23.578 --> 03:25.125
How old did you guys say you are?

03:25.497 --> 03:27.841
We're 13! So, technically a teen!

03:27.999 --> 03:31.173
All right. I like your moxie, kid.
Let me get my stuff.

03:32.754 --> 03:35.633
Since when are we 13?
Is this a leap year?

03:35.799 --> 03:36.721
Come on, Mabel!

03:36.883 --> 03:39.636
This is our chance to hang out
with, you know, the cool kids.

03:39.803 --> 03:40.850
And Wendy and whatever.

03:41.054 --> 03:45.059
I knew it! You love her!
Love! Love! Love! Love! Love!

03:45.267 --> 03:46.439
- Oh, hey, what's that?
- Huh?

03:47.811 --> 03:49.188
(SPITTING)

03:51.440 --> 03:52.362
Hurry UP-

03:52.566 --> 03:54.318
BOTH: (CHANTING)
In the belly! In the belly!

03:54.484 --> 03:55.406
(THOMPSON GROANING)

03:55.610 --> 03:57.829
BOTH: In the belly! In the belly!

03:58.029 --> 03:59.076
(ALL CHEERING)

03:59.239 --> 04:00.365
Yeah!

04:02.451 --> 04:03.577
ALL: Wendy.

04:03.785 --> 04:05.253
Wendy. Wendy.

04:05.454 --> 04:07.752
Hey, guys, these are my pals from work.
Mabel and Dipper.

04:08.081 --> 04:09.879
I chewed my gum
so it looks like a brain!

04:11.001 --> 04:15.177
She's not much for first impressions.
Unlike this guy!

04:17.007 --> 04:18.259
This <i>gl-IY---</i>

04:19.134 --> 04:21.387
So, are you, like, babysitting, or...

04:21.595 --> 04:22.938
(SCOFFS) Come on, Robbie.

04:23.138 --> 04:25.061
- Guys, this is Lee and Nate.
-(GROANS)

04:25.265 --> 04:26.141
(LAUGHS)

04:26.349 --> 04:27.771
- Tambry.
- Hi.

04:27.976 --> 04:30.820
WENDY: Thompson, who once ate
a run-over waffle for 50 cents.

04:31.021 --> 04:32.273
Don't tell them that.

04:32.439 --> 04:35.192
WENDY: And Robbie.
You can probably figure him out.

04:35.358 --> 04:38.032
Yeah, I'm the guy
who spray-painted the water tower.

04:38.236 --> 04:39.533
Oh, you mean the big muffin!

04:39.738 --> 04:41.536
Um, it's a giant explosion!

04:43.241 --> 04:44.208
(CHUCKLING)

04:44.409 --> 04:45.956
LEE: It kind of does look like a muffin!

04:46.119 --> 04:47.041
(BOTH LAUGHING)

04:49.790 --> 04:52.339
Let's hurry it up, guys.
I got big plans for tonight. Huh?

04:52.542 --> 04:53.589
LEE: Yeah, all right,
let's get out of here.

04:53.794 --> 04:54.841
THOMPSON: Come on, guys,
get in the car.

04:55.003 --> 04:55.925
LEE: Ow-ow!

04:56.213 --> 04:57.965
Sorry, kid. I ride shotgun, all right?

05:01.802 --> 05:02.849
(CAR ENGINE STARTING)

05:03.053 --> 05:04.726
Okay. Just, before we go,

05:04.930 --> 05:08.355
my mom said you guys aren't allowed
to punch the roof anymore, so...

05:08.809 --> 05:10.982
ALL: Thompson!
Thompson! Thompson!

05:11.186 --> 05:13.985
Thompson! Thompson! Thompson!

05:24.366 --> 05:26.869
(LAUGHING)
This is gonna blow someone's mind.

05:27.077 --> 05:27.999
Mabel. Please.

05:28.161 --> 05:32.792
What? Am I embarrassing you
in front of your new (SHOUTING) girl...

05:33.625 --> 05:34.842
(MUFFLED SPEECH)

05:35.001 --> 05:37.299
Ugh! Did you just lick my hand?

05:39.339 --> 05:41.137
<i>MAN ON</i> TV: <i>You're watching
the black-and-white-period-piece</i>

05:41.341 --> 05:43.014
<i>old-lady-boring movie channel.</i>

05:43.510 --> 05:44.432
Kids!

05:44.636 --> 05:46.730
I can't find the remote
and I refuse to stand up.

05:46.930 --> 05:48.853
<i>Stay tuned for the Friday night
movie, The Duchess Approves,</i>

05:49.057 --> 05:51.276
<i>starring Sturly Stembleburgiss
as The Duchess</i>

05:51.476 --> 05:53.478
<i>and Grampton St. Rumpterfabble
as the irascible coxswain,</i>

05:53.645 --> 05:55.272
<i>Saunterblugget Hampterfuppinshire.</i>

05:55.438 --> 05:56.439
Kids!

06:00.235 --> 06:02.988
No! No!

06:07.492 --> 06:09.039
WENDY: There it is, fellas.

06:09.202 --> 06:11.045
The condemned Dusk 2 Dawn.

06:11.246 --> 06:12.293
LEE: (CHUCKLING) Whoa!

06:12.497 --> 06:14.044
- Neat-o!
- LEE: Awesome.

06:14.249 --> 06:17.469
Why did they shut it down?
It's like a health code violation or...

06:17.669 --> 06:18.670
Try murder!

06:18.879 --> 06:21.849
Some folks died in there.
The place has been haunted ever since.

06:22.048 --> 06:24.722
This town has such a colorful history!

06:24.885 --> 06:26.853
What? Are you guys serious?

06:27.053 --> 06:29.055
Yeah, "We're all gonna die!"

06:29.264 --> 06:31.642
Chill out, man.
It's not as bad as it looks.

06:35.437 --> 06:36.609
Come on, Dipper.

06:36.813 --> 06:40.113
(LAUGHING NERVOUSLY) Okay.
Okay, just, got to get a foothold.

06:40.317 --> 06:41.910
Dude, your sister did it.

06:42.110 --> 06:43.327
(GIBBERISH)

06:44.487 --> 06:46.535
Hey, you know what?
Just, there you go.

06:46.740 --> 06:47.662
(GRUNTING)

06:48.241 --> 06:49.584
LEE: (LAUGHS) Sorry, dude.

06:50.035 --> 06:52.208
NATE: Good job throwing the kid
off the fence, genius.

06:52.412 --> 06:53.709
LEE: Your mom's a genius.

06:53.914 --> 06:54.881
(ROBBIE GRUNTING)

06:56.082 --> 06:58.551
(CHUCKLING) This place is amazing.

06:58.919 --> 07:00.387
I think it's stuck.

07:00.587 --> 07:01.679
Let me take a crack at it.

07:01.880 --> 07:02.972
Oh, yeah. I can't get in,

07:03.173 --> 07:06.518
but I'm sure Junior here
is gonna break it down like Hercules.

07:06.718 --> 07:09.392
Come on. Leave him alone.
He's just a little kid.

07:17.312 --> 07:18.279
(GRUNTING)

07:18.563 --> 07:20.691
TAMBRY: Whoa. Kid.
What are you doing?

07:21.775 --> 07:22.742
(GRUNTING)

07:24.986 --> 07:27.409
MABEL: Go, Dipper!
Punch that metal thing!

07:28.657 --> 07:30.751
Hey, Dipper, take it easy!

07:30.951 --> 07:32.578
Who wants to bet he doesn't make it?

07:35.455 --> 07:37.253
MABEL: Cool.
LEE: Awesome!

07:37.624 --> 07:39.626
Good call inviting this little maniac!

07:39.834 --> 07:42.053
Your new name is Doctor Funtimes!

07:42.253 --> 07:44.927
- All right!
- THOMPSON: Too cool. Yeah, man!

07:45.757 --> 07:46.758
Nice work.

07:49.386 --> 07:51.059
THOMPSON: Do you guys
really think it's haunted?

07:51.262 --> 07:53.560
LEE: Nah! Thompson,
are you kidding me?

07:53.723 --> 07:55.191
NATE: Come on, shut up, man.
(LAUGHING)

07:59.813 --> 08:00.814
(ALL EXCLAIMING IN AWE)

08:01.022 --> 08:02.365
LEE: Whoa! Dude.
WENDY: No way.

08:02.565 --> 08:03.612
LEE: Look at this place.
ROBBIE: Ah, no way.

08:03.817 --> 08:05.490
NATE: Wow. What is this?
ROBBIE: Check it out!

08:05.694 --> 08:08.948
Oh, man,
it's even creepier than I imagined!

08:15.620 --> 08:17.122
Yep. It's dust.

08:21.167 --> 08:23.545
Hey, dude. Where do you think
they keep the dead bodies?

08:23.753 --> 08:24.879
(LAUGHS) Shut up, man.

08:25.088 --> 08:27.591
Guys! Check it out!
You think these still work?

08:29.217 --> 08:31.390
(MACHINES POWERING UP)

08:33.429 --> 08:34.556
THOMPSON: Nice.
NATE: Whoa!

08:34.722 --> 08:36.270
- ROBBIE: So cool.
- Unbelievable.

08:36.474 --> 08:37.475
Jackpot!

08:37.642 --> 08:39.188
So what are we gonna do now?

08:39.394 --> 08:40.441
Anything we want.

08:45.817 --> 08:47.069
- THOMPSON: Take that!
- Cool!

08:48.028 --> 08:49.245
-(GRUNTS)
-(LAUGHING)

08:49.446 --> 08:50.368
(GRUNTS)

08:51.865 --> 08:53.913
ROBBIE: Put 'em in, put 'em in.
Three at a time, three at a time!

08:54.409 --> 08:55.376
(ALL CHEERING)

08:56.119 --> 08:57.086
(DIPPER CHUCKLES)

09:00.540 --> 09:05.262
Oh, my gosh! Smile Dip! I thought
this stuff was banned in America!

09:05.462 --> 09:06.554
Maybe they had a good reason?

09:06.755 --> 09:08.382
Ooh! (LAUGHING)

09:12.427 --> 09:13.394
(GOBBLES)

09:13.595 --> 09:14.938
NATE: Hey, come here, man!
We got it ready!

09:15.138 --> 09:16.606
Whatever it is, I'll do it!

09:17.182 --> 09:18.809
(LAUGHING) Thompson!

09:19.017 --> 09:20.769
Dipper, this night is, like, legendary.

09:20.977 --> 09:22.399
- Really?
- Just look around.

09:22.562 --> 09:23.529
The guys are bonding.

09:23.730 --> 09:24.697
(LAUGHING)

09:25.398 --> 09:27.947
I've never even seen Tambry
look up from her phone this long.

09:28.860 --> 09:31.158
And your sister seems to be
going nuts for that Smile Dip.

09:31.404 --> 09:32.576
(GROANING)

09:32.822 --> 09:35.792
Maybe I've had too much.
What do you think?

09:36.743 --> 09:38.165
(INDISTINCT GROWLING)

09:40.080 --> 09:42.959
Would you like to eat my candy paws?

09:43.458 --> 09:45.460
Of course, you little angel!

09:51.174 --> 09:53.927
You know, Dipper, I wasn't sure
if you could hang with our crew at first.

09:54.135 --> 09:56.513
But you're surprisingly mature
for your age!

09:56.679 --> 09:58.352
Yes. Yes, I am.

10:00.600 --> 10:02.443
NATE: Hey, guys! We need more ice!

10:03.394 --> 10:04.566
I'm on it!

10:12.153 --> 10:13.120
(GROWLS)

10:14.197 --> 10:15.164
(SCREAMS)

10:16.658 --> 10:17.625
(PANTING)

10:28.419 --> 10:31.343
What was that? I thought I heard
some lady screaming back here.

10:31.548 --> 10:32.640
You freaking out, kid?

10:32.799 --> 10:35.518
(NERVOUS SHUDDER) No!
No, I'm cool. Everything's cool.

10:35.718 --> 10:36.890
Then what's all this about?

10:37.095 --> 10:41.271
Oh. That's, uh... (GASPS) Hey, look!
Dancy Pants Revolution!

10:41.641 --> 10:43.518
The game that tricks people
into exercising.

10:43.810 --> 10:45.107
WENDY: All right, I'm down.
NATE: Let's go!

10:45.311 --> 10:47.439
(NERVOUS CHUCKLE)
Yeah! Let's all... Let's all go play that.

10:51.401 --> 10:52.277
(THOMPSON PANTS)

10:52.485 --> 10:53.828
MALE GAME ANNOUNCER:
Dance! <i>Hurry</i> up!

10:54.028 --> 10:55.951
BOTH: Go! Go! GO! Go!

10:56.156 --> 10:57.999
Wow, he's really terrible at this.

10:58.199 --> 11:00.748
(NERVOUS CHUCKLE)
Yeah, yeah. That's great.

11:07.834 --> 11:09.256
Huh!

11:10.837 --> 11:12.009
I'll be right back.

11:12.213 --> 11:13.180
(PHONE LINE RINGING)

11:13.464 --> 11:15.432
Come on, Grunkle Stan, pick up!

11:15.633 --> 11:16.759
(GROANS) What is he doing?

11:17.093 --> 11:18.015
(PHONE RINGING)

11:18.219 --> 11:19.266
<i>DUCHESS:
I don't care about dukes or commoners</i>

11:19.470 --> 11:21.939
<i>or His Royal Highness
Lionel of Cornwall!</i>

11:22.140 --> 11:23.858
<i>I'm not afraid anymore, Mother!</i>

11:24.058 --> 11:26.277
<i>Duchess, I forbid you!</i>

11:26.477 --> 11:30.903
<i>I may be a duchess,
but I'm also a woman!</i>

11:31.107 --> 11:34.452
Yes! Yes! In your face, Elizabeth!

11:34.652 --> 11:36.746
(SOBBING) It's just like my life!

11:37.739 --> 11:38.786
In a way.

11:39.115 --> 11:40.412
(DIAL TONE SOUNDING)

11:40.617 --> 11:41.869
Mabel, I need your advice!

11:42.076 --> 11:43.953
We're hanging out
in a haunted convenience store,

11:44.120 --> 11:45.121
I can't get a hold of Grunkle Stan,

11:45.330 --> 11:47.503
and if I try to say anything about it
to any of these guys,

11:47.707 --> 11:49.835
they'll just think I'm a scared little kid
or something.

11:50.001 --> 11:50.968
(GURGLING)

11:52.212 --> 11:53.509
Mabel?

11:53.713 --> 11:58.093
The future is in the past!
Onwa rds, Aoshima!

12:01.846 --> 12:03.063
(ALARM BLARES)

12:03.431 --> 12:05.479
Mabel! How many of these did you eat?

12:05.642 --> 12:07.815
Bleventeen...

12:08.019 --> 12:10.397
Oh, man! Oh, man! Oh, man! Oh, man!

12:10.897 --> 12:11.864
(CHUCKLES)

12:16.778 --> 12:19.201
Whoa! Guys!
You might wanna see this.

12:20.031 --> 12:21.908
TAMBRY: What?
NATE: What the heck?

12:22.242 --> 12:23.209
Whoa!

12:23.409 --> 12:25.582
- Then the rumors are true!
-(GULPS)

12:25.787 --> 12:27.164
Dude, I dare you to lie down in it.

12:27.372 --> 12:29.090
Good idea! Go lie down in it.

12:29.374 --> 12:31.126
(CHUCKLES) I'm a dead body! Look!

12:33.419 --> 12:35.592
Wait! Maybe let's not do that.

12:35.797 --> 12:37.265
This guy's scared!

12:37.465 --> 12:39.684
All I'm saying is, why tempt the fates?

12:39.842 --> 12:45.269
I mean, what if this place,
really is haunted?

12:45.890 --> 12:46.857
- WENDY: Aw, come on.
- Boo!

12:47.058 --> 12:47.934
Come on.

12:48.142 --> 12:50.236
Just take it down a notch,
Captain Buzzkill.

12:50.436 --> 12:52.154
But I thought I was Doctor Funtimes!

12:52.355 --> 12:55.575
Well, you're acting like
Captain Buzzkill, right?

12:56.734 --> 12:58.452
Yeah, little bit.

12:58.653 --> 12:59.700
(SIGHING)

12:59.904 --> 13:03.659
Status update, trapped in store
with insane 9-year-old.

13:03.866 --> 13:08.542
I'm not a 9-year-old!
I'm 13! Technically a teen!

13:09.831 --> 13:10.957
(ALL TALKING IN DISTINCTLY)

13:18.131 --> 13:19.098
(GASPS)

13:19.799 --> 13:20.766
WENDY: Whoa!

13:21.217 --> 13:22.218
-(ALL GASP)
- What?

13:22.969 --> 13:24.312
Status update...

13:24.637 --> 13:25.763
(DIPPER READING)

13:30.018 --> 13:31.486
(SCREAMING)

13:31.853 --> 13:33.196
(ALL SCREAMING)

13:34.439 --> 13:35.406
(SCREAMING)

13:36.524 --> 13:38.242
Tambry! Tambry!

13:38.401 --> 13:39.573
Can you hear us?

13:41.070 --> 13:42.242
What are we supposed to do?

13:42.447 --> 13:44.074
I don't know, man! I don't know!

13:44.240 --> 13:46.242
- Let's just go already!
- Thompson!

13:46.451 --> 13:49.250
Wait! (PANTS)
I've almost got the high score!

13:51.205 --> 13:52.172
(THOMPSON SCREAMING)

13:53.166 --> 13:54.292
Huh? What?

13:54.500 --> 13:56.548
GAME <i>ANNOUNCER: Time to shake
what your momma gave you!</i>

13:56.753 --> 13:59.757
Oh, no! Help! So many arrows!

13:59.922 --> 14:01.424
<i>You're a dance machine!</i>

14:01.632 --> 14:03.259
No! You're a dance machine!

14:03.468 --> 14:04.344
(sesame)

14:04.552 --> 14:05.804
- Oh, no!
- Thompson.

14:06.012 --> 14:07.730
Forget him! Let's go!

14:10.558 --> 14:12.560
What the... Guys, it's locked!

14:12.810 --> 14:13.936
Out of my way!

14:14.604 --> 14:15.571
(GRUNTS)

14:16.564 --> 14:17.531
(ALL SCREAMING)

14:18.149 --> 14:22.154
Everybody wait. Whatever is doing this
has to have some kind of reason.

14:22.320 --> 14:25.369
Maybe if we could just figure out
what it is, then they'll let us out of here!

14:25.573 --> 14:28.076
"Ooh! They'll let us out of here!"
Yeah, that makes a lot of sense.

14:28.242 --> 14:30.119
I don't know, guys,
maybe he's got a point.

14:30.328 --> 14:33.298
Yeah, right, I'm sure the ghost
just wants to talk about its feelings.

14:33.790 --> 14:35.542
(SCREAMING)

14:37.377 --> 14:38.799
What?

14:38.961 --> 14:41.589
I'm bonkers for eating you alive!

14:41.798 --> 14:43.926
No! (SCREAMING)

14:44.133 --> 14:48.684
Lee! Okay, okay. I'm with you, kid.
100%, man!

14:50.640 --> 14:52.062
(AS MALE GHOST) <i>Welcome.</i>

14:52.266 --> 14:53.142
(ALL SHRIEKING)

14:53.351 --> 14:54.352
They got Mabel!

14:54.519 --> 14:56.942
<i>Welcome to your graves,
young trespassers.</i>

14:57.146 --> 14:58.193
(EVIL LAUGHTER)

14:58.856 --> 15:00.824
We're super sorry
for hanging out in your store.

15:01.025 --> 15:03.528
Yeah, can we just go now
and leave forever?

15:04.237 --> 15:07.081
<i>Well, okay. You're free to go.</i>

15:07.615 --> 15:08.582
(DOOR BEEPS)

15:08.783 --> 15:11.662
<i>But before you leave,
hot dogs are now half off.</i>

15:11.869 --> 15:14.247
<i>I know it might be crazy,
but you gotta try these dogs.</i>

15:14.831 --> 15:15.957
(BOTH SCREAMING)

15:16.999 --> 15:18.922
<i>Just kidding about the hot dog sale!</i>

15:19.085 --> 15:20.678
Just let us out of here already!

15:20.878 --> 15:22.505
<i>I don't like your tone!</i>

15:25.133 --> 15:26.385
No. No.

15:28.928 --> 15:32.307
What? No! I'm a hot dog.

15:32.515 --> 15:34.188
<i>It begins.</i>

15:37.019 --> 15:37.986
Whoa!

15:42.400 --> 15:43.322
(GRUNTING)

15:46.028 --> 15:46.995
Ah!

15:47.405 --> 15:50.454
<i>Welcome to your home for all eternity!</i>

15:50.658 --> 15:51.625
Dipper. What do we do?

15:51.826 --> 15:53.078
Duck!

15:53.244 --> 15:54.587
Quick! In there!

15:57.707 --> 15:59.084
(BOTH PANTING)

15:59.625 --> 16:00.968
What do they want from us?

16:01.169 --> 16:02.261
Revenge, I guess?

16:02.462 --> 16:03.463
What did we do wrong?

16:03.671 --> 16:05.389
Okay, let's try to figure out
the pattern here.

16:05.590 --> 16:06.887
Why was each person taken?

16:07.091 --> 16:09.640
Tambry was texting.
Thompson was playing a video game.

16:09.802 --> 16:12.351
Lee was being sarcastic.
It doesn't make any sense.

16:12.555 --> 16:15.354
Yeah, I mean, those are all
just normal, teenage things.

16:16.559 --> 16:18.653
Wendy, say that last part again.

16:18.853 --> 16:20.070
Normal teenage things?

16:20.271 --> 16:22.365
Of course! Stay here until I get back.

16:24.484 --> 16:26.031
Dude! What are you doing!

16:29.739 --> 16:30.956
HEY, ghost!

16:31.157 --> 16:32.079
(GROWLS)

16:33.618 --> 16:35.291
I've got something to tell you!

16:37.121 --> 16:39.419
I'm not a teenager!

16:41.584 --> 16:42.551
(GRUNTS)

16:44.086 --> 16:45.554
(LAUGHING)

16:45.755 --> 16:47.678
Well, why didn't you say so?

16:47.840 --> 16:48.762
(MABEL GRUNTS)

16:48.966 --> 16:49.842
(GROANS)

16:50.051 --> 16:51.644
How old did you say you were?

16:52.970 --> 16:53.971
(SIGHS)

16:54.472 --> 16:57.191
I'm 12. Technically not a teen.

16:57.391 --> 17:00.486
When we were alive,
teenagers were a scourge on our store.

17:00.686 --> 17:04.862
Always sassafrassin' customers
with their boomy boxes

17:05.066 --> 17:07.239
and disrespectful short pants.

17:07.401 --> 17:09.654
<i>So we decided to up and ban them.</i>

17:09.862 --> 17:14.083
<i>But they retaliated
with this newfangled rap music.</i>

17:14.242 --> 17:17.086
FEMALE GHOST:
<i>The lyrics, they were so hateful.</i>

17:17.286 --> 17:20.881
<i>Homework's wack! And so are rules!
Tucking in your shirt's for fools!</i>

17:21.040 --> 17:22.462
[[511

17:22.666 --> 17:23.714
FEMALE GHOST: <i>It</i> was <i>so</i> shocking,

17:23.917 --> 17:25.670
<i>we were stricken down
with double heart attacks.</i>

17:25.877 --> 17:27.175
-(HEARTBEAT POUNDING)
-(BOTH GROANING)

17:28.214 --> 17:29.181
(MACHINE FLATLINING)

17:30.258 --> 17:32.807
That's why we hate teenagers so much!

17:33.010 --> 17:34.182
Don't we, honey?

17:35.012 --> 17:36.264
But they're my friends.

17:36.472 --> 17:38.566
Isn't there anything
I can do to help them?

17:38.724 --> 17:40.977
There is one thing.

17:41.185 --> 17:43.813
Do you know any funny little dances?

17:44.230 --> 17:46.653
Uh... Is there anything else I can do?

17:46.857 --> 17:48.985
[[511

17:49.193 --> 17:50.160
Okay, okay, okay!

17:50.319 --> 17:56.702
Um... Well, I do know
the lamby-lamby dance.

17:56.909 --> 18:00.163
But I can't really do it
without a lamb costume.

18:01.455 --> 18:02.422
Oh!

18:02.623 --> 18:04.921
Well. There it is.

18:05.585 --> 18:06.507
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

18:06.711 --> 18:11.057
(SINGING) <i>Well, who wants
a Iamby, Iamby, Iamby?</i>

18:11.257 --> 18:13.055
<i>I do! I do!</i>

18:13.259 --> 18:16.138
<i>So, go up and greet your
mammy, mammy, mammy</i>

18:16.345 --> 18:17.847
<i>Hi there! Hi there!</i>

18:18.055 --> 18:19.307
<i>So, march, march, march
around the daisies</i>

18:19.515 --> 18:21.768
Yes, yes! More! More!

18:21.976 --> 18:27.403
<i>Don't, don't, don't
you forget about the baby</i>

18:29.734 --> 18:33.784
That was some fine girly dancing, boy.

18:34.030 --> 18:35.282
Your friends are free.

18:36.532 --> 18:39.456
Well, I don't think you have to worry
about us coming back, so...

18:44.624 --> 18:46.001
(ALL SCREAMING)

18:48.628 --> 18:49.595
Ugh!

18:49.837 --> 18:53.216
I'm never going to eat
or do anything ever again.

18:53.424 --> 18:54.801
Hey! There's still some left.

18:55.009 --> 18:55.851
Evil!

18:56.052 --> 18:58.896
What? What happened
after everything went crazy?

18:59.096 --> 19:00.598
You are not going to believe it.

19:00.806 --> 19:03.605
The ghosts appeared,
and Dipper had to...

19:05.853 --> 19:07.025
Uh... (CLEARS THROAT)

19:07.438 --> 19:09.065
Dipper just grabbed a bat

19:09.273 --> 19:11.116
and started beating ghosts down,
left and right.

19:11.317 --> 19:15.367
And then the ghosts got all scared
and ran away like a couple of little girls.

19:15.571 --> 19:17.573
- It was insane!
- No way!

19:18.199 --> 19:19.746
NATE: Doctor Funtimes!

19:24.872 --> 19:26.795
Well, I'm probably scarred for life.

19:26.999 --> 19:28.842
Yeah, that was pretty crazy.

19:29.001 --> 19:32.050
Think I'm gonna go stare at a wall
for a while and rethink everything.

19:32.254 --> 19:35.224
Hey, next time we hang out,
let's stay at the Mystery Shack, okay?

19:35.424 --> 19:37.472
(LAUGHING) Next time? Yeah!

19:37.677 --> 19:41.648
Yeah! Let's hang out
at the Shack! Yeah!

19:43.015 --> 19:44.267
Next time.

19:46.769 --> 19:47.986
(GROANING)

19:48.813 --> 19:51.316
What kind of sick joke is this?

19:59.031 --> 20:02.160
Ah! The wedding.
I've waited so long for this.

20:02.368 --> 20:03.790
Oh! Look at her in that dress.

20:04.036 --> 20:04.958
(PEOPLE GASPING ON TV)

20:05.121 --> 20:07.340
Count Lionel? What's he doing here?

20:07.540 --> 20:09.292
COUNT <i>LIONEL:
I've come to reclaim my bride!</i>

20:09.500 --> 20:11.969
You had your chance
at the cotillion, you!

20:12.169 --> 20:14.137
<i>You had your chance
at the cotillion, you!</i>

20:14.338 --> 20:15.806
That's what I'm saying!

20:16.006 --> 20:17.303
(SCREAMS IN FRUSTRATION)

20:21.053 --> 20:22.020
Ah...

20:22.638 --> 20:23.764
Couldn't find the remote.
